1
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:50,171
<i>- [Man On Radio] Give me audio on that, please.</i>
<i>- [Men Laughing]</i>

2
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:54,050
<i>[Man #2 On Radio]</i>
<i>Right turn on Royal.</i>

3
00:00:54,154 --> 00:00:57,123
<i>[Man #1]</i>
<i>Can you zoom in? All right. Now pan right.</i>

4
00:00:57,223 --> 00:01:01,319
<i>[Woman On Radio]</i>
<i>Yes, that's affirmative. Male, late 30s.</i>

5
00:01:01,428 --> 00:01:03,988
<i>[Man #1] Group of six males, Quadrant 9.</i>
<i>Give me the middle one.</i>

6
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:05,758
<i>[Man #3 On Radio]</i>
<i>N.G. Not a match.</i>

7
00:01:05,865 --> 00:01:08,425
<i>[Man #1]</i>
<i>Agent 4-86, squawk and ident. Need your position.</i>

8
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:10,799
<i>[Man #4 On Radio]</i>
<i>Camera's on Decatur, now online.</i>

9
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,337
<i>I'm heading north on Clinton.</i>

10
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:14,669
<i>[Man #1]</i>
<i>Let's get a sweep moving southeast on Toulouse.</i>

11
00:01:14,774 --> 00:01:17,800
<i>Strike that.</i>
<i>On Conti- 800 block.</i>

12
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:21,938
<i>[Man #4]</i>
<i>I'm going to change position.</i>

13
00:01:22,048 --> 00:01:24,448
<i>- [Man #3] Two out of five, no good.</i>
<i>- [Man #1] That's no good.</i>

14
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:27,145
<i>Come back around on Exchange</i>
<i>and head north.</i>

15
00:01:27,253 --> 00:01:29,448
<i>[Man #5]</i>
<i>I'm moving onto Burgundy Street now.</i>

16
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:32,252
<i>It's got some dropouts on the feed there.</i>

17
00:01:32,358 --> 00:01:34,553
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>Possible target heading northeast on Bourbon.</i>

18
00:01:34,661 --> 00:01:36,629
<i>Fifty yards from St. Louis.</i>

19
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:39,960
<i>[Man #1] Southwest corner.</i>
<i>Target is wearing a red shirt and shoulder bag.</i>

20
00:01:40,066 --> 00:01:43,365
<i>[Man #6] I see the target.</i>
<i>I'm too far out for a facial lock.</i>

21
00:01:43,470 --> 00:01:47,634
<i>[Man #7]</i>
<i>I've got him. Red shirt.</i>

22
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:50,106
<i>[Man #8]</i>
<i>No good. Face is turned.</i>

23
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:52,371
<i>[Man #7]</i>
<i>Static camera missed him too.</i>

24
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:56,779
<i>[Woman] Gator's got eyes on him.</i>
<i>I'm heading back around the perimeter.</i>

25
00:01:56,883 --> 00:02:00,148
<i>[Man #9]</i>
<i>Gator, he's a 120 yards ahead to the left.</i>

26
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:02,278
<i>[Gator]</i>
<i>I'm right behind him.</i>

27
00:02:02,388 --> 00:02:04,379
Looks real close.

28
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:06,516
Can't get a clear shot.

29
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:10,323
<i>[Man #1] He's coming up on your left.</i>
<i>Suspect in red continuing on Conti Street.</i>

30
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:13,797
<i>Rabbit got him. Full face.</i>

31
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,800
Give me a sec.

32
00:02:18,771 --> 00:02:20,739
Beginning scan.

33
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:26,406
Negative. It's not a match.

34
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:28,378
Okay, Bulldog, take the northwest quad.

35
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:30,813
<i>Gator, hold firm, cover that east bank.</i>

36
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:35,244
Samuel's in position?

37
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:37,152
We're just waiting on Miles, sir.

38
00:02:37,257 --> 00:02:39,691
<i>[Man #1] Need a whole new sweep</i>
<i>of the area starting in Quad 1.</i>

39
00:02:39,792 --> 00:02:43,455
<i>Let's get all bank "A"cameras online.</i>

40
00:02:43,696 --> 00:02:47,291
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>Danny? You're not feeding the dog, are you?</i>

41
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,368
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>No. I'm looking for my badge.</i>

42
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:52,529
They give you two things when you're a cop-
a gun and a badge.

43
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:56,040
I have one.
I can't find my badge.

44
00:02:56,142 --> 00:02:59,202
- It's on the thingy.
- The thing, the thing?

45
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:02,338
I was just over by the thing.
It's not there.

46
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:04,780
Shortie, remember our plan.
You're gonna stay strong, I'm gonna give you food.

47
00:03:04,884 --> 00:03:07,079
Just don't tell Mom
I gave you that, all right?

48
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:10,782
Daniel Fisher. Hmm?

49
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:13,017
I'm tryin' to build
the world's most dominant pug.

50
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:15,390
He's going through a bulking phase.
Look at him.

51
00:03:15,495 --> 00:03:18,191
Come here, Shortie.
Come on. Daddy's bad.

52
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:20,528
Come here.
I'll show you the thingy.

53
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:22,225
The thing.
"It's by the thing."

54
00:03:22,335 --> 00:03:24,633
<i>I was just by the thing.</i>
<i>It's not there.</i>

55
00:03:24,737 --> 00:03:27,228
- I was just-
- [Laughing] The thingy.

56
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:29,274
- This is the thing.
- Yeah.

57
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,741
- I didn't know you meant that thing.
- Course not.

58
00:03:31,844 --> 00:03:36,110
<i>It's here. You know,</i>
<i>I still got, like, 10 minutes.</i>

59
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,309
Yeah? It only takes you two, honey.
Come on.

60
00:03:38,418 --> 00:03:41,546
- I think it's a strong two.
- [Laughs]

61
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:49,957
Go to work.
Be safe, okay?

62
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:54,628
Okay. Go.

63
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:56,429
Love you, Shortie.

64
00:03:58,004 --> 00:04:00,734
- Hey, Hank!
- Hey, Molly!

65
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,673
[Chuckles]
Come on.

66
00:04:03,776 --> 00:04:07,940
Aw, shit. I am definitely not smarter
than a fifth grader.

67
00:04:08,047 --> 00:04:10,811
<i>[Female Dispatcher, Indistinct]</i>

68
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,817
<i>Do you need backup?</i>

69
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,819
Hey, man. What's going on?

70
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:18,618
So you, uh-you gotta get permission from
the old lady and the dog now to come to work?

71
00:04:18,725 --> 00:04:22,456
- Just the dog.
- [Laughs]

72
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:24,928
<i>Hey, homework.</i>

73
00:04:25,031 --> 00:04:27,124
F.B.I.'s tracking this guy through the Quarter.
They need some hand-holding.

74
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:34,472
Coming out of the hotel.

75
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,269
<i>Target matches four out of five points.</i>

76
00:04:36,376 --> 00:04:38,207
Gator's on Royal, 200 block.

77
00:04:38,311 --> 00:04:42,008
All available agents, scramble.
We need a clear lock. Get audio in place.

78
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:45,016
He's moving towards Bourbon.
I'm 50 yards back.

79
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:48,986
<i>Come on, people.</i>
<i>I can't afford to lose this guy again.</i>

80
00:04:49,088 --> 00:04:51,022
<i>I'm in position,</i>
<i>target heading towards me.</i>

81
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:53,024
<i>Clear shot.</i>

82
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:56,489
[Beeping]

83
00:04:56,596 --> 00:04:58,655
Hold position.

84
00:04:58,765 --> 00:05:00,494
- Sir, the locals need-
- Shut up!

85
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,568
Show me that Irish bastard.

86
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:17,310
Confirmed. All teams,
we have a positive I.D. on Miles Jackson.

87
00:05:17,417 --> 00:05:20,318
<i>You want to see the face of the devil?</i>
<i>There it is.</i>

88
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:24,618
<i>Brought down Trans Atlantic Flight 212.</i>
<i>Bombed the American Embassy in Frankfurt.</i>

89
00:05:24,724 --> 00:05:28,182
The man decapitated his own brother
for blowing a deal in Tangiers.

90
00:05:28,294 --> 00:05:30,421
It's game day, people.
Let's go.

91
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:32,555
Got him.

92
00:05:34,767 --> 00:05:37,895
- He's got his cell phone out now.
- Sir, he's making the call.

93
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:39,869
[Cell Phone Rings]

94
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:43,733
Hey, open up Samuel's feed.

95
00:05:43,843 --> 00:05:45,572
It's an incoming call, sir.
Still encrypted.

96
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:51,246
Fifteen minutes.
The abandoned wharf on Permission Way.

97
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:53,876
Miles is bringing the weapons,
and we're making the exchange.

98
00:05:56,622 --> 00:05:58,920
<i>[Man] I got three tapped cameras,</i>
<i>including the harbor crane.</i>

99
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:02,017
- I need Team 1 to get me set up inside.
- Samuel, remember our deal.

100
00:06:02,128 --> 00:06:05,359
You ever want to see your brother again,
you do as I say when I say it.

101
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:08,866
We get Miles, we get the weapons,
you and Joshua get your freedom.

102
00:06:08,968 --> 00:06:11,232
<i>- Clear?</i>
<i>- Claro.</i>

103
00:06:12,638 --> 00:06:13,764
Now we dance.

104
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:21,040
- No! Hey, hey. No, no, no, no, no.
- Hang on. He stopped.

105
00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:24,605
Let's see.
He takes your bishop knight to c4...

106
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:26,617
pawn to a7, rook to block.

107
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:29,882
He takes your queen.
It's all over but the crying.

108
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:33,550
Try, uh, pawn to a6.
It's better.

109
00:06:35,495 --> 00:06:37,395
He's heading east.

110
00:06:38,931 --> 00:06:40,831
[Whistles]

111
00:06:40,933 --> 00:06:42,730
<i>[Gator]</i>
<i>He's hailing a cab.</i>

112
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:45,827
Mobile Unit 6 has video on him,
hundred yards back.

113
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:48,805
<i>Send N.O.P.D. the new pics on Miles.</i>

114
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:51,877
Have them establish
a 10-block perimeter around the wharf.

115
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:55,175
- Sir, should you call the director?
- No.

116
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:58,182
This is the first time Miles has been
out in the open in two years.

117
00:06:58,284 --> 00:07:00,269
The director has no idea
you're about to cut a deal.

118
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:00,980
There is no deal.

119
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:04,113
We use Samuel and Joshua to get to Miles.
We bring 'em all down.

120
00:07:04,223 --> 00:07:08,751
Nobody's going anywhere, Ray.
This time, he's not getting away from me.

121
00:07:11,864 --> 00:07:16,096
Just give me the scoop, man.
So, you gonna pop the question, or what?

122
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:19,330
I'm just saying, you know, you move in
with the lady, the ring usually comes next.

123
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,873
Bro, it's been two weeks.

124
00:07:21,974 --> 00:07:25,307
- And?
- Yeah, you've lived with, like, 14 different girls.

125
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:29,211
Why, yes, I did. But I'm sexier than you.
[Laughing]

126
00:07:29,315 --> 00:07:31,681
I mean, if a freakishly large man
such as yourself...

127
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:34,981
is gonna keep a fine woman like Molly,
you're gonna have to put her in cuffs.

128
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:48,563
E.T.A: two minutes.
Cameras are up inside the wharf.

129
00:08:15,461 --> 00:08:17,361
<i>[Miles On Radio]</i>
<i>Punctual, Sam. I like that.</i>

130
00:08:17,463 --> 00:08:20,432
<i>- We got audio now. Reading five by five.</i>
- Okay, we're in first position.

131
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,558
All teams, on my mark.

132
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:27,105
We get Miles to lead us to the location
of the guns, we proceed with extract.

133
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:33,244
Okay, so... this is how
this rodeo is gonna work.

134
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,712
<i>You give me the briefcase...</i>

135
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:39,182
I give you the P.D.A.
with the coordinates to the weapons.

136
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:42,277
- It's all very simple.
- No.

137
00:08:44,056 --> 00:08:46,547
I can't do this.

138
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:49,457
Don't you do this, you son of a bitch.

139
00:08:49,562 --> 00:08:51,792
You can't do what?

140
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:54,560
- [Static Crackling]
- I set you up.

141
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,635
<i>[Beeping]</i>

142
00:08:59,171 --> 00:09:03,301
<i>The F.B.I. knows you're here.</i>
<i>They're watching us right now.</i>

143
00:09:03,409 --> 00:09:05,707
They-They know you're here.

144
00:09:06,979 --> 00:09:09,641
And now I'm never gonna
see my brother again.

145
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:22,760
Half an hour, Lake Pontchartrain Causeway.

146
00:09:22,862 --> 00:09:25,057
You bring me my brother,
I'll bring you Miles.

147
00:09:25,164 --> 00:09:27,428
That is, of course,
if he makes it that long.

148
00:09:27,533 --> 00:09:29,000
[Gunshot]

149
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:42,679
- Holy shit.
- Hey, let's move.

150
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:44,764
Get me an outside feed.
Give me the outside feeds!

151
00:09:44,765 --> 00:09:45,114
You got it.

152
00:10:16,749 --> 00:10:19,398
Sir, we need to stop 'em
before they get to the bridge.

153
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:20,344
Get me a 20 on Joshua.

154
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:22,944
- Samuel is gonna try to get his brother.
- You want to make a deal?

155
00:10:23,055 --> 00:10:24,955
Ray, pick up the phone!

156
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:31,359
The F.B.I. told us exactly where
they were positioned. Go around.

157
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:33,364
<i>Okay.</i>

158
00:10:34,934 --> 00:10:37,300
You all right?

159
00:10:41,273 --> 00:10:43,571
It's gonna bruise like a bitch.

160
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:50,714
You're lucky I didn't aim any lower.

161
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:53,011
Man, it's just like those pansy-ass feds.

162
00:10:53,119 --> 00:10:55,644
I mean, they call us, we jump right away.

163
00:10:55,755 --> 00:10:59,816
<i>We call them, city's under seven feet of water-</i>
<i>Hey, five days. Take it easy.</i>

164
00:10:59,925 --> 00:11:02,189
Those guys skin my ass, Danny,
they really do.

165
00:11:02,294 --> 00:11:05,923
Look at this guy-
arms trafficking, espionage, murder.

166
00:11:06,032 --> 00:11:08,728
Hell, he even sold two dirty bombs
in Paris last year.

167
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:10,392
Interpol says he's got
two more on the market.

168
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,165
Like the city needs more to deal with?

169
00:11:13,272 --> 00:11:16,537
I mean, really, why can't they take that crap
someplace else- Kansas, Iowa?

170
00:11:16,642 --> 00:11:19,008
- Helsinki.
- [Laughs]

171
00:11:19,111 --> 00:11:22,342
<i>[Dispatcher] All units, we're at black.</i>
<i>F.B.I. requests assistance.</i>

172
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:24,143
<i>Sending target information.</i>

173
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,343
<i>Eight male suspects, three vehicles</i>
<i>heading to Lake Pontchartrain Causeway.</i>

174
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:29,910
- Sounds like the feds dropped the ball again.
- Surprised?

175
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:32,422
[Siren Wailing]

176
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:44,796
Someone broke into the safe house.
They took Joshua and killed our agents.

177
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:47,202
- He did it again.
- How do you want to proceed with the convoy?

178
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:50,702
Well, take 'em!

179
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:51,435
Take 'em.

180
00:11:57,582 --> 00:12:01,609
I threw in an extra five percent,
for treating my brother and I so well.

181
00:12:03,054 --> 00:12:05,079
- Was it any trouble getting him out?
- For me?

182
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:10,628
Nah. For the two guards
I had to kill, maybe.

183
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:13,289
- And he's waiting at the airfield?
- Yeah, he's there right now.

184
00:12:13,398 --> 00:12:15,662
Why don't you give him a call?

185
00:12:17,269 --> 00:12:19,669
<i>You know what the funny thing is, Sam?</i>

186
00:12:19,771 --> 00:12:21,932
If I hadn't have found out the F.B.I.
was holding your brother...

187
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,940
<i>as a bargaining chip to catch me...</i>

188
00:12:24,042 --> 00:12:27,409
<i>you'd have gone along with this whole
double-cross without so much as a consideration.</i>

189
00:12:27,512 --> 00:12:30,106
<i>- [Cell Phone Ringing]</i>
- And I'd be out of my hard-earned cash.

190
00:12:30,215 --> 00:12:34,481
The F.B.I. would probably
have me in custody...

191
00:12:34,586 --> 00:12:36,486
and you and your douche bag brother...

192
00:12:36,588 --> 00:12:40,024
would be holding hands somewhere
in the south of France.

193
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:42,093
[Rings]

194
00:12:43,528 --> 00:12:46,156
[Echoing]
Yeah? Hello.

195
00:12:46,264 --> 00:12:50,997
I'm sorry. Joshua can't come to the phone
right now, but thanks for the ride.

196
00:13:06,451 --> 00:13:08,919
[Sirens Wailing]

197
00:13:19,213 --> 00:13:21,204
Oldest trick in the book, Sam.

198
00:13:21,315 --> 00:13:23,306
Turn their heads with one hand...

199
00:13:23,417 --> 00:13:26,648
quietly slip out the back with the other.

200
00:13:38,432 --> 00:13:40,297
Later.

201
00:13:47,942 --> 00:13:51,036
- Right on time, baby.
- Aren't I always?

202
00:13:52,413 --> 00:13:54,074
Mmm!

203
00:14:01,455 --> 00:14:03,821
Show me.

204
00:14:10,131 --> 00:14:14,830
<i>We can finally afford that pony</i>
<i>that you've always wanted.</i>

205
00:14:14,936 --> 00:14:18,929
[Giggles]
I'll drive.

206
00:14:20,408 --> 00:14:21,807
- Whoo!
- Right.

207
00:14:25,146 --> 00:14:29,378
<i>[Man On Radio] F.B.I. update. Suspects in custody,</i>
<i>but Miles Jackson is still at large.</i>

208
00:14:29,483 --> 00:14:32,941
<i>Looking for gray van, Louisiana plates:</i>
<i>Alpha-Golf-November-803.</i>

209
00:14:33,054 --> 00:14:35,682
<i>- Stand by.</i>
- Unit 14 en route for Lower Nine.

210
00:14:37,725 --> 00:14:40,819
- Whoa!
- [Truck Horn Honks]

211
00:14:42,563 --> 00:14:44,895
Uh, my bad.

212
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:49,534
<i>I didn't even see that guy.</i>

213
00:14:50,738 --> 00:14:53,502
[Siren Wailing]

214
00:14:58,613 --> 00:15:00,547
Turn around.

