00:33:45,887 --> 00:33:48,219
Hey, Danny.
Danny, that's not gonna happen, okay?

445
00:33:48,323 --> 00:33:51,053
- We're gonna find her. We're gonna get her back.
- Molly, come on. Pick up.

446
00:33:51,159 --> 00:33:52,251
Pick up!

447
00:33:53,728 --> 00:33:56,595
[Miles]
Molly Porter's phone.

448
00:33:56,698 --> 00:33:59,633
- Let me talk to her.
- [Beeps]

449
00:33:59,734 --> 00:34:02,362
[On Speaker]
How do you know she's not dead already?

450
00:34:02,470 --> 00:34:03,869
I'm just teasing, Danny.

451
00:34:03,972 --> 00:34:07,669
Come on. Come on.
Where's your sense of humor?

452
00:34:07,776 --> 00:34:09,676
[Quiet Grunting]

453
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:15,010
- Here. Say hello to your boyfriend.
- Danny, please.

454
00:34:15,116 --> 00:34:17,641
<i>- We're in a silver va-</i>
- Molly! Molly, where are you?

455
00:34:17,752 --> 00:34:20,220
That one was for free.

456
00:34:20,322 --> 00:34:22,290
<i>The rest you'll have to earn.</i>

457
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:24,324
I'm gonna find you.

458
00:34:24,426 --> 00:34:26,986
I'm gonna hunt you down,
and I'm gonna kill you.

459
00:34:27,095 --> 00:34:29,359
<i>Well, you know what?</i>
<i>I look forward to that, Danny.</i>

460
00:34:29,464 --> 00:34:32,661
It's a game.
What, you like games, don't you?

461
00:34:32,767 --> 00:34:36,168
Mousetrap, Monopoly, naked Twister.

462
00:34:36,271 --> 00:34:38,330
This one's called 12 Rounds.

463
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:42,308
<i>Round 1- I took your house.</i>
<i>Round 2- I took Molly.</i>

464
00:34:42,410 --> 00:34:46,141
The only way to keep her alive-
you do exactly what I say when I say it.

465
00:34:46,247 --> 00:34:50,707
<i>If you're still standing after all 12 rounds,</i>
<i>well, then you'll have won her back.</i>

466
00:34:50,819 --> 00:34:54,152
You gotta be kidding me. You can't expect me
to believe that you're gonna keep-

467
00:34:54,255 --> 00:34:56,553
Well-You'll believe
what I tell you to believe, Danny.

468
00:34:56,658 --> 00:34:57,920
<i>I don't think you've got much choice.</i>

469
00:34:58,526 --> 00:35:00,323
<i>Okay. Round 3.</i>

470
00:35:00,428 --> 00:35:04,091
In 15 minutes I will be calling
a particular cell phone in the city.

471
00:35:04,199 --> 00:35:08,898
Why don't you return to where we first met,
see if you can pick up my scent once again?

472
00:35:12,207 --> 00:35:14,402
Okay, uh, Molly said she
was in a silver van, okay?

473
00:35:14,509 --> 00:35:16,443
They can't be more
than six blocks from here.

474
00:35:16,544 --> 00:35:18,876
- Put out an A.P.B., get a trace on Molly's cell.
- Okay.

475
00:35:41,302 --> 00:35:43,862
<i>[Miles's Voice]</i>
<i>... your name?</i>

476
00:35:43,972 --> 00:35:45,906
<i>[Echoing]</i>
<i>Officer Fisher.</i>

477
00:35:49,411 --> 00:35:52,642
<i>- [Dog Barking]</i>
<i>- I don't see anything.</i>

478
00:35:52,747 --> 00:35:55,739
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Maybe we're in the wrong place.</i>

479
00:35:55,850 --> 00:35:58,284
No. This is where we stopped the car.
This is where it started.

480
00:35:58,386 --> 00:36:01,617
And this is where he shot me in the ass.
But I don't see anything.

481
00:36:01,723 --> 00:36:04,658
- How much time?
- Uh, we got 10 minutes.

482
00:36:04,759 --> 00:36:08,718
<i>I definitely think we're</i>
<i>in the wrong place, Danny.</i>

483
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:13,062
<i>No, wait. I could be wrong.</i>
<i>That's- That's not from Katrina.</i>

484
00:36:13,168 --> 00:36:15,762
- That's today's date.
<i>- You're right.</i>

485
00:36:15,870 --> 00:36:18,430
That's a code. Uh-

486
00:36:18,540 --> 00:36:20,770
We got degrees.
We got clocks.

487
00:36:20,875 --> 00:36:23,173
Yeah, those aren't real clocks though.
There's-There's no hours.

488
00:36:23,278 --> 00:36:24,306
Uh, countdown?

489
00:36:24,307 --> 00:36:27,977
No, no, no. It's just, uh,
two degrees, two clocks.

490
00:36:29,083 --> 00:36:32,917
Degrees, minutes, seconds.

491
00:36:33,021 --> 00:36:34,921
"X."

492
00:36:35,023 --> 00:36:38,424
Longitude and latitude. That's a location.
That's where we're gonna find the phone.

493
00:36:38,526 --> 00:36:41,086
Longitude and latitude. How the hell
do you know about this stuff, Danny?

494
00:36:41,196 --> 00:36:43,255
Eighth-grade geography, brother. Let's go.

495
00:36:43,364 --> 00:36:46,527
[Hank]
Okay, read 'em back to me.

496
00:36:46,634 --> 00:36:50,331
No, no, no, no. Twenty-nine degrees,
57 minutes, three seconds.

497
00:36:51,372 --> 00:36:53,101
Yeah. Got it.
317 Decatur.

498
00:36:53,208 --> 00:36:55,836
317 Decatur?
That's my brother's firehouse.

499
00:37:02,083 --> 00:37:05,678
<i>- [Cell Phone Ringing]</i>
- Ooh-hoo-hoo!

500
00:37:05,787 --> 00:37:07,755
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>All right. Who's up?</i>

501
00:37:07,856 --> 00:37:10,723
Hey, bro. We're doing an all-day Ping-Pong
tourney. Why don't you come on down?

502
00:37:10,825 --> 00:37:13,555
- You at the station?
- Why are you shouting?

503
00:37:13,661 --> 00:37:16,994
Get everybody out. There may be a bomb
in the house. I'll be there in two minutes.

504
00:37:19,801 --> 00:37:21,894
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Movin' out now.</i>

505
00:37:34,782 --> 00:37:36,977
I need the computers patched.
I need a full phone bank.

506
00:37:36,978 --> 00:37:38,309
<i>Yeah, they're clear upstairs.</i>

507
00:37:38,419 --> 00:37:41,217
- Everybody out?
- Yeah.

508
00:37:41,322 --> 00:37:43,847
Danny, you really think this guy
put a bomb in the firehouse?

509
00:37:43,958 --> 00:37:47,018
This guy blew up my house. He took Molly.
I have no idea what he's gonna do next.

510
00:37:47,128 --> 00:37:47,684
Fifteen seconds.

511
00:37:47,685 --> 00:37:49,562
He said he was gonna call a
particular cell phone here.

512
00:37:49,664 --> 00:37:51,894
<i>Everybody, cell phones out.</i>

513
00:37:54,435 --> 00:37:58,895
<i>Five, four, three, two, one.</i>

514
00:38:01,776 --> 00:38:03,710
<i>[Cell Phone Ringing, Faint]</i>

515
00:38:06,047 --> 00:38:08,880
You hear that?
It's right there. It's right there.

516
00:38:08,983 --> 00:38:11,713
<i>[Rings]</i>

517
00:38:11,819 --> 00:38:13,582
- [Rings]
<i>- [Woman] Can I help you?</i>

518
00:38:13,688 --> 00:38:15,918
Hey, Jansen.
Give me a second.

519
00:38:16,024 --> 00:38:19,221
- Hello?
- [Miles] Look at that, Danny. Right on time.

520
00:38:19,327 --> 00:38:22,421
You've just earned yourself
extra minutes on the next task.

521
00:38:22,664 --> 00:38:26,395
<i>- [Fire Call Signal Rings, Blares]</i>
<i>- Go. I'm on three.</i>

522
00:38:26,501 --> 00:38:30,301
<i>And speak of the devil,</i>
<i>there's the bell for Round 4.</i>

523
00:38:30,405 --> 00:38:34,364
There's a fire
in the Orleans Savings and Loan.

524
00:38:34,475 --> 00:38:37,706
<i>In the memory chip</i>
<i>of the phone you're holding...</i>

525
00:38:37,812 --> 00:38:41,248
<i>are the numbers of two security deposit boxes</i>
<i>located on the 10th floor.</i>

526
00:38:41,349 --> 00:38:45,149
<i>To win, simply grab those boxes...</i>

527
00:38:45,253 --> 00:38:47,744
by 5:55 exactly...

528
00:38:47,855 --> 00:38:51,951
or there's gonna be an early knockout.

529
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:54,324
You gotta be shittin' me.

530
00:38:54,429 --> 00:38:56,989
Uh, not enough time.
I'm just gonna come in.

531
00:38:57,098 --> 00:39:00,659
<i>Yeah. I'll be right there.</i>

532
00:39:00,768 --> 00:39:03,134
Hey, hey. Tel-com is up on your phone.

533
00:39:03,237 --> 00:39:05,865
They just think they found the van
that Miles used to take Molly.

534
00:39:05,974 --> 00:39:08,875
I'm gonna go back and set up a war room,
all right? You okay?

535
00:39:15,116 --> 00:39:18,813
<i>Hey, hey.</i>
<i>Hey, hey, hey! Focus.</i>

536
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:21,354
Molly needs you to focus.
All right?

537
00:39:21,456 --> 00:39:24,118
We gotta do this.
You gotta help me find her.

538
00:39:26,094 --> 00:39:28,858
When have I ever
let you down before? Huh?

539
00:39:28,963 --> 00:39:30,863
You're right.

540
00:39:30,965 --> 00:39:33,365
All right?
Go get this done.

541
00:39:44,412 --> 00:39:46,778
- Detective Fisher?
- Yeah.

542
00:39:46,881 --> 00:39:48,849
Ray Santiago, F.B.I.
This is Inspector George Aiken.

543
00:39:48,950 --> 00:39:51,680
We understand that Miles Jackson's
resurfaced in the area.

544
00:39:51,786 --> 00:39:53,845
- What'd you just say?
- Miles Jackson.

545
00:39:53,955 --> 00:39:55,946
- We heard he tried to contact you-
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

546
00:39:56,057 --> 00:39:59,026
The guy breaks out of prison,
F.B.I. knows about it, and nobody tells me?

547
00:39:59,127 --> 00:40:01,561
- We understand that you're upset, Danny-
- It was none of your business.

548
00:40:01,663 --> 00:40:04,063
You can keep on crying about
what you did and didn't know...

549
00:40:04,165 --> 00:40:08,124
or you can tell us everything that happened
this morning since you woke up.

550
00:40:08,236 --> 00:40:11,069
That is, if you want your girl back.

551
00:40:11,172 --> 00:40:14,801
<i>- Engine two, let's move out.</i>
- Danny, you catching a ride?

552
00:40:14,909 --> 00:40:16,877
We're your best chance, Danny.

553
00:40:16,978 --> 00:40:20,470
Tell us what we wanna know,
we'll tell you what you wanna know.

554
00:40:20,581 --> 00:40:25,245
- [Siren Wailing, Horn Blowing]
- You better talk as fast as they drive.

555
00:40:33,828 --> 00:40:36,058
[Chattering, Exclaiming]

556
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,865
There was a prison break
in Florida two weeks ago.

557
00:40:40,968 --> 00:40:43,198
<i>Miles and the inmates took the guards,</i>
<i>killed the warden...</i>

558
00:40:43,304 --> 00:40:45,431
and demanded 30 cars
to drive out of the prison.

559
00:40:45,540 --> 00:40:48,907
- And you gave them to them?
- Wasn't exactly our choice, Danny.

560
00:40:49,010 --> 00:40:51,945
<i>The bureau gave them cars</i>
<i>with kill switches and remote door locks.</i>

561
00:40:52,046 --> 00:40:54,412
<i>The inmates get three blocks away from the yard,</i>
<i>National Guard comes in...</i>

562
00:40:54,515 --> 00:40:56,710
puts everyone back in their cells.

563
00:40:56,818 --> 00:40:59,844
- Everyone except Miles.
- Would you please just shut up?

564
00:40:59,954 --> 00:41:02,047
You're killing me with the whining.

565
00:41:02,156 --> 00:41:04,215
<i>You have no idea</i>
<i>what you're up against, do you?</i>

566
00:41:04,325 --> 00:41:06,259
I know you "arrested" him,
but you still don't know.

567
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:09,022
<i>The fact Miles Jackson</i>
<i>has your girlfriend-</i>

568
00:41:09,130 --> 00:41:11,030
mmm, that interests me very little.

569
00:41:11,132 --> 00:41:13,862
<i>The fact that he's done something</i>
<i>that he never does...</i>

570
00:41:13,968 --> 00:41:16,766
the fact that he's
shown himself in the city-

571
00:41:16,871 --> 00:41:19,203
that interests me quite a bit more.

572
00:41:19,307 --> 00:41:22,208
You wanna catch Miles?
That's fine.

573
00:41:22,310 --> 00:41:24,870
I wanna keep Molly alive,
and I know what I gotta do.

574
00:41:29,417 --> 00:41:32,545
Just stay the hell out of my way.

575
00:41:36,157 --> 00:41:38,557
I guess he didn't hear me
about the whining.

576
00:41:38,659 --> 00:41:40,320
Sir, this is exactly what Miles wants.

577
00:41:40,428 --> 00:41:42,988
<i>We should stop Danny</i>
<i>before somebody gets hurt.</i>

578
00:41:43,097 --> 00:41:45,964
Danny? What, are you best friends now?

579
00:41:46,067 --> 00:41:48,262
<i>If Danny keeps playing the game,</i>
<i>Miles is distracted.</i>

580
00:41:48,369 --> 00:41:52,533
Miles is distracted,
he might make a mistake-

581
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:54,608
and I'll bury him.

582
00:41:55,777 --> 00:41:57,642
Come on!

583
00:41:57,745 --> 00:41:59,804
- Dave.
- Danny.

584
00:41:59,914 --> 00:42:03,281
<i>- How much time?</i>
- Six minutes.

585
00:42:05,953 --> 00:42:08,319
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Let's go! Let's head up the south stairwell.</i>

586
00:42:08,422 --> 00:42:10,947
Smoke on 10, guys.
Come on. Let's go! Let's go!

587
00:42:15,963 --> 00:42:18,989
Let's go.
Let's get a line up there.

588
00:42:20,234 --> 00:42:23,499
Let's go!
Keep moving! Keep moving.

589
00:42:23,604 --> 00:42:25,504
<i>The guys are going up the stairwell now!</i>

590
00:42:25,606 --> 00:42:28,541
<i>Come on, guys.</i>
<i>Let's move it!</i>

591
00:42:30,278 --> 00:42:33,645
[Chattering]

592
00:42:37,151 --> 00:42:38,812
Listen up!

593
00:42:38,920 --> 00:42:41,684
Listen up.
I need everybody.

594
00:42:41,789 --> 00:42:46,123
All right. Thirty-two minutes ago,
Molly Porter was taken from the Canal Street ferry.

595
00:42:46,227 --> 00:42:50,163
We need every security camera, every
possible witness, every vehicle plate number.

596
00:42:51,799 --> 00:42:54,324
This asshole calls again,
I wanna know where he is.

597
00:42:54,435 --> 00:42:57,131
<i>I wanna know what he's doing.</i>
<i>I wanna find him before he so much as thinks...</i>

598
00:42:57,238 --> 00:42:59,172
about touching one hair on her head.

599
00:42:59,273 --> 00:43:02,572
This could be your girlfriend,
could be your wife.

600
00:43:02,677 --> 00:43:05,145
Could be any one of us.

601
00:43:05,246 --> 00:43:08,807
All right.
This asshole cannot win.

602
00:43:11,285 --> 00:43:14,777
<i>[Firefighters Chattering, Shouting]</i>

603
00:43:20,928 --> 00:43:23,658
<i>- [Man] We got some spare air bottles?</i>
- [Coughing]

604
00:43:30,838 --> 00:43:34,330
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Clear that backroom!</i>

605
00:43:34,442 --> 00:43:36,603
- Dave!
- Yeah.

606
00:43:38,279 --> 00:43:40,509
Watch yourself.
[Grunting]

607
00:43:43,784 --> 00:43:46,753
[Coughing]

608
00:43:46,854 --> 00:43:49,152
How much time?

609
00:43:49,257 --> 00:43:51,384
Two minutes.

610
00:43:53,995 --> 00:43:56,555
Hold this.

611
00:43:59,634 --> 00:44:01,363
<i>It's 590. 591.</i>

612
00:44:01,469 --> 00:44:03,903
Right there.

613
00:44:05,239 --> 00:44:07,969
<i>[Grunting]</i>

614
00:44:13,481 --> 00:44:16,211
[Beeping]

615
00:44:17,885 --> 00:44:19,876
Danny.

616
00:44:24,158 --> 00:44:27,924
- [Exhales]
<i>- [Cell Phone Ringing]</i>

617
00:44:28,029 --> 00:44:30,554
[Miles]
Surprise!

618
00:44:30,665 --> 00:44:33,828
Sometimes victory is not
all it's cracked up to be.

619
00:44:33,935 --> 00:44:36,597
Eh, Danny? Round 5!

620
00:44:36,704 --> 00:44:40,606
<i>Two pounds of explosives</i>
<i>packed inside one of these boxes.</i>

621
00:44:40,708 --> 00:44:44,474
You now have less than seven minutes
to cross the 23 city blocks...

622
00:44:44,578 --> 00:44:46,978
between here
and the Nicholls Street Wharf.

623
00:44:47,081 --> 00:44:49,174
<i>Arrive at the wharfany later,</i>
<i>the bomb goes off.</i>

624
00:44:49,283 --> 00:44:52,480
<i>The other box contains</i>
<i>the clue to the next round.</i>

625
00:44:52,586 --> 00:44:55,987
<i>See, in your time constraints,</i>
<i>you might wanna use the fire truck for this one.</i>

626
00:44:56,090 --> 00:45:00,186
<i>Oh, yeah. And don't forget</i>
<i>to wear the hat and use the siren.</i>

627
00:45:01,963 --> 00:45:03,760
Seven minutes?

628
00:45:03,864 --> 00:45:06,424
We won't even be out of the building
in seven minutes.

629
00:45:06,534 --> 00:45:08,502
That's if we take the stairs.

630
00:45:09,770 --> 00:45:12,864
<i>Danny!</i>

631
00:45:14,809 --> 00:45:17,505
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Ten is clear! Repeat, no fire!</i>

632
00:45:17,611 --> 00:45:20,944
<i>Just a bunch of smoke bombs!</i>

633
00:45:22,984 --> 00:45:24,815
What are you doing?

634
00:45:24,919 --> 00:45:26,944
<i>Get them all out of the building!</i>

635
00:45:27,054 --> 00:45:30,490
You got gloves?
Give them here.

636
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:36,618
When you get out of here, you get to Atlanta,
you find Mom and you stay with her.

637
00:45:36,731 --> 00:45:39,564
Make sure she's safe.
I don't want this guy havin' another chance.

638
00:45:39,667 --> 00:45:42,465
- Anchor this down.
- Danny-

639
00:45:42,570 --> 00:45:44,697
Anchor it down!

640
00:45:46,974 --> 00:45:49,465
Danny, you can't do this!

641
00:45:49,577 --> 00:45:52,171
<i>[Man Shouting, Indistinct]</i>

642
00:45:56,951 --> 00:45:59,852
[Exclaiming, Shouting]

643
00:46:02,823 --> 00:46:05,257
Oh, shoot!
Do you see that man?

644
00:46:07,695 --> 00:46:10,596
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Folks, I'm gonna ask you to back up, please.</i>

645
00:46:21,375 --> 00:46:23,070
[Grunting]

646
00:46:27,515 --> 00:46:29,073
[Gasping]

647
00:46:30,851 --> 00:46:32,944
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>You got triage ready to go?</i>

648
00:46:34,955 --> 00:46:38,049
- Danny!
- [Groans]

649
00:46:40,194 --> 00:46:43,925
<i>Everybody accounted for?</i>
<i>Have 'em all respond on tac channel two.</i>

650
00:46:44,031 --> 00:46:45,931
<i>They're moving out now!</i>

651
00:46:52,973 --> 00:46:56,238
Hey, what are you doing?
Look out!

652
00:46:56,343 --> 00:46:59,904
<i>- [Engine Revs]</i>
<i>- You, out of the truck now!</i>

653
00:47:00,014 --> 00:47:02,915
<i>- Hey, what are you doin'?</i>
- [Horn Blows]

654
00:47:05,820 --> 00:47:08,448
[Siren Wailing]

655
00:47:22,169 --> 00:47:24,103
[Horn Blowing]

656
00:47:26,006 --> 00:47:27,667
<i>[Danny On Phone]</i>
<i>Did you get the trace?</i>

657
00:47:27,775 --> 00:47:30,972
<i>No, he's using an encrypted signal.</i>
<i>We can't even pull a number to start a trace.</i>

658
00:47:31,078 --> 00:47:33,478
- [Siren Wailing]
- What's that sound, Danny?

659
00:47:33,581 --> 00:47:37,608
- I'm driving a fire truck.
- Are you sure that's such a good idea right now?

660
00:47:37,718 --> 00:47:38,946
Oh!

661
00:47:40,754 --> 00:47:43,120
[Horn Blows]

662
00:47:49,363 --> 00:47:54,096
Call the bomb squad!
Get them to Nicholls Street Wharf! I gotta go!

663
00:47:54,201 --> 00:47:55,463
Stay with him.

664
00:47:59,973 --> 00:48:02,066
[Horn Honks]

665
00:48:03,176 --> 00:48:05,440
- Hey! Look out!
- [Screaming]

666
00:48:25,231 --> 00:48:28,029
[Chattering, Laughing]

667
00:48:30,737 --> 00:48:33,706
[Siren Wailing, Horn Blowing]

668
00:48:43,182 --> 00:48:45,116
[Screaming]

669
00:49:02,402 --> 00:49:04,165
[Fast Beeping]

670
00:49:08,374 --> 00:49:11,070
No, no, no!
What are you doin'?

671
00:49:19,552 --> 00:49:20,985
Yo, hey! Hey! Chill!

672
00:49:27,226 --> 00:49:28,693
Sorry!

673
00:49:33,366 --> 00:49:35,596
[Horn Honking]

674
00:49:57,824 --> 00:50:01,726
[Tires Screeching]

675
00:50:24,517 --> 00:50:27,850
- [Siren Stops]
- Shut down the timers, Miles. I'm here.

676
00:50:27,954 --> 00:50:32,823
<i>Well done, Danny, but I'm sorry to say,</i>
<i>you seem to be a bit late to the party.</i>

677
00:50:36,779 --> 00:50:38,474
[Bell Dings]

678
00:50:40,383 --> 00:50:43,978
[Beeping]

679
00:50:56,332 --> 00:51:00,166
It was the bell. The bell signals
the start of the next round.

680
00:51:00,269 --> 00:51:03,170
Oh, you're finally starting
to get the hang of this.

681
00:51:03,272 --> 00:51:05,263
I wanna speak to Molly.

682
00:51:05,375 --> 00:51:08,970
How about I do you one better?
How about I show her to you?

683
00:51:09,078 --> 00:51:12,980
<i>As I said, the clue to the next round</i>
<i>is in the box you so deftly hung on to.</i>

684
00:51:13,082 --> 00:51:15,209
<i>You put two and two together...</i>

685
00:51:15,318 --> 00:51:18,116
you might have quite the reunion.

686
00:51:19,322 --> 00:51:22,052
Tell me you didn't kill anybody
with that thing.

687
00:51:28,464 --> 00:51:30,364
I need a saw.

688
00:51:36,906 --> 00:51:40,342
<i>[Man] All right. Let's drain this thing</i>
<i>and get it back to the yard.</i>

689
00:51:45,748 --> 00:51:48,216
It's clear.

690
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:54,380
- Thought you guys were gonna catch him.
- We switched out your SI M card.

691
00:51:54,490 --> 00:51:57,391
We're tapped into your phone.
We can track you wherever you go.

692
00:51:57,493 --> 00:52:00,929
Miles will call again, Danny. When he does,
keep him on the line for 30 seconds.

693
00:52:01,030 --> 00:52:03,692
- That's all we need.
- Miles's phone's encrypted. You can't trace it.

694
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:05,768
That's funny.
We're the F.B.I., not Mayberry P.D.

695
00:52:05,868 --> 00:52:07,927
All we need is 30 seconds.

696
00:52:08,037 --> 00:52:12,201
All teams, listen up, listen up!
We have a location.

697
00:52:12,308 --> 00:52:16,039
<i>It's the Hotel Monteleone.</i>
<i>I repeat. It's the Hotel Monteleone.</i>

698
00:52:16,145 --> 00:52:20,514
I need SWAT, and I need K-9,
and I need all of you there. Now!

699
00:52:20,616 --> 00:52:23,380
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

700
00:52:28,124 --> 00:52:31,423
<i>Get the elevators shut down.</i>
<i>Secure the street. K-9 unit inside.</i>

701
00:52:31,527 --> 00:52:34,553
- Get against the wall.
- Down! Everybody down!

702
00:52:38,034 --> 00:52:40,798
Blue team, seal all the exits.
I need snipers on the roof.

703
00:52:40,903 --> 00:52:44,304
Shut down all communication in and out
of the building, and start with the dogs.

704
00:52:44,407 --> 00:52:48,309
Ray, pull the tapes.
I need to know what room this key is for.

705
00:52:48,411 --> 00:52:50,174
<i>- Where's your control room?</i>
<i>- [Man] Right this way.</i>

706
00:52:50,279 --> 00:52:51,576
<i>[Santiago]</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>

707
00:52:53,549 --> 00:52:55,414
It's clean.

708
00:53:03,025 --> 00:53:06,324
- Clear!
- Clear. Fisher!

